{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(_:)-1xuni","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(_:)-46imp","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(_:)-4ld1t","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(_:)-6bawz","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(_:)-827x2","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(dmy:month:year:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(julian:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(raw:)-5r9lx","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(raw:)-8w9i2","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(retainingRaw:)-39bfb","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/init(retainingRaw:)-745yi"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/ptr"]},{"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/new(dmy:month:year:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/new(julian:)"]},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date\/DateProtocol-Implementations"],"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a struct for calendrical calculations."}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/date"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Date"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" data structure represents a day between January 1, Year 1,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and sometime a few thousand years in the future (right now it will go","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the year 65535 or so, but [method"},{"code":"GLib.Date.set_parse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] only parses up to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"year 8000 or so - just count on “a few thousand”). ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"type":"text","text":" is meant to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"represent everyday dates, not astronomical dates or historical dates","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or ISO timestamps or the like. It extrapolates the current Gregorian","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calendar forward and backward in time; there is no attempt to change"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the calendar to match time periods or locations. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" does not store","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time information; it represents a day."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation has several nice features; it is only a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"64-bit struct, so storing large numbers of dates is very efficient. It"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can keep both a Julian and day-month-year representation of the date,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"since some calculations are much easier with one representation or the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"other. A Julian representation is simply a count of days since some","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"fixed day in the past; for "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" the fixed day is January 1, 1 AD."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(“Julian” dates in the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" API aren’t really Julian dates in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"technical sense; technically, Julian dates count from the start of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Julian period, Jan 1, 4713 BC).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" is simple to use. First you need a “blank” date; you can get a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"dynamically allocated date from [ctor","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.new"},{"type":"text","text":"], or you can declare an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"automatic variable or array and initialize it by calling [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.clear"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A cleared date is safe; it’s safe to call [method"},{"code":"GLib.Date.set_dmy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and the other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"mutator functions to initialize the value of a cleared date. However, a cleared date"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is initially invalid, meaning that it doesn’t represent a day that exists.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It is undefined to call any of the date calculation routines on an invalid date.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If you obtain a date from a user or other unpredictable source, you should check","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"its validity with the [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.valid"},{"type":"text","text":"] predicate. [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.valid"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is also used to check for errors with [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.set_parse"},{"type":"text","text":"] and other functions"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that can fail. Dates can be invalidated by calling [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.clear"},{"text":"] again.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is very important to use the API to access the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" struct. Often only the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"day-month-year or only the Julian representation is valid. Sometimes neither is valid."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use the API.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"GLib also features ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDateTime"},{"text":" which represents a precise time.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","type":"reference"},{"text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Date","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Date"}],"title":"Date","externalID":"s:4GLib4DateC","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Date/init(retainingRaw:)-745yi":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"retainingRaw"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SV","text":"UnsafeRawPointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"title":"init(retainingRaw:)","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/date\/init(retainingraw:)-745yi","kind":"symbol"